							<h1>Hadar 3.4-2.8ma</h1>
						<p>The Hadar site is located in the Afar triangle region of Ethiopia (shown in inset, right). It was discovered in 1968 along the Kada Hadar and Ounda Hadar tributaries of the Awash River.
The site itself sits in a large sedimentary basin between the Ethiopian Escarpment and the volcanic axis of the central Afar. The sediments at Hadar accumulated over a period that spanned the late Miocene to the early Pleistocene. 
